<p>The padding utility classes allow you to quickly apply consistent
inner spacing within elements using a standardized spacing scale. All
classes support responsive design with mobile-first breakpoints.</p>
<h3 id="doc-examples">Examples</h3>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;p-7&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;px-0&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;py-5&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;pt-1&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;pl-lg-3&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
<h3 id="doc-basic-syntax">Basic Syntax</h3>
<pre class="html"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;p-{value}&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;px-{value}&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;pt-{value}&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;pl[-breakpoint]-{value}&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;!-- and so on --&gt;</code></pre>
<ul>
<li><p><code>{value}</code>: <code>0</code> to <code>7</code></p></li>
<li><p>Direction prefixes:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>p</code>: all sides</li>
<li><code>px</code>: left &amp; right</li>
<li><code>py</code>: top &amp; bottom</li>
<li><code>pt</code>: top</li>
<li><code>pr</code>: right</li>
<li><code>pb</code>: bottom</li>
<li><code>pl</code>: left</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
